(197, 1, '2013-06-29 16:01:28', '2013-06-29 16:01:28', '<strong>GUIDELINES ON STUDENT ON-THE-JOB TRAINING AT THE MANILA INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT AUTHORITY</strong>\r\n<div><strong>I.RATIONALE </strong></div>\r\n<div>  The MIAA regularly accepts students aspiring to pursue their on-the-job training  (OJT) with the Authority as part of the school’s curriculum requirement. Thus, it is necessary that systems, policies and procedures be formulated to ensure consistency in the processing of applicants for On-The-job-Training and management of student trainees.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>II. PURPOSE AND SCOPE</strong></div>\r\n<div>    This Memorandum Circular prescribes the guidelines, rules and regulations on OJT requirements; deployment and completion of on-the-job training. It shall apply student trainees at MIAA and to all MIAA offices that will accommodate students trainees.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>III. DEFINITION AND TERMS</strong></div>\r\n<div>    1. On-the-Job Training (OJT) – a time-bounded educational and hands-on work experience for students at MIAA.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>IV. POLICIES AND PROCEDURES</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n   A. POLICIES\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">    School Endorsement</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">    Bases of Deployment</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">    Discontinuation of On-the-Job Training</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">    Remunerationh</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">    Attire</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">    Working Hours</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">    Daily time Record (DTR)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nB. PROCEDURES\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Screening</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;"> All on-the-Job training applicants shall undergo a preliminary interview to be conducted the HRDD Representative.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">On-the-job training applicants shall submit the following requirements:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>             a.) School Recommendation</div>\r\n<div>             b.) Application Letter stating:</div>\r\n<div>             c.) Resume</div>\r\n<div>                •  Objectives/s</div>\r\n<div>                •  Area/s of interest</div>\r\n<div>             d.) Recent pictures – 2x2 (2 pcs.); 3R half body (1 pc.)</div>\r\n<div>             e.) Waiver</div>\r\n<div>             f.) NBI Clearance – Original copy and 2 photocopies</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">The said documents shall be reviewed for completeness and evaluated by the Supervisor of HRDD.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">After the requirements have been completed and reviewed on-the-job training applicants shall undergo an interview with the Manager or Supervisor of HRDD.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Results of Interview shall only be either Pass or Fail.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>V. SUPERSESSION CLAUSE</strong></div>\r\n<div>    All MIAA issuance in conflict herewith are superseded accordingly.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>VI. EFFECTIVITY</strong></div>\r\n<div>     This Memorandum Circular shall take effect immediately.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Guidelines', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'guidelines', '', '', '2013-06-29 16:21:17', '2013-06-29 16:21:17', '', 18, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=197', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(198, 1, '2013-06-29 15:57:24', '2013-06-29 15:57:24', 'GUIDELINES ON STUDENT ON-THE-JOB TRAINING AT THE MANILA INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT AUTHORITY\n<div><strong>I.RATIONALE </strong></div>\n<div>  The MIAA regularly accepts students aspiring to pursue their on-the-job training  (OJT) with the Authority as part of the school’s curriculum requirement. Thus, it is necessary that systems, policies and procedures be formulated to ensure consistency in the processing of applicants for On-The-job-Training and management of student trainees.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div><strong>II. PURPOSE AND SCOPE</strong></div>\n<div>    This Memorandum Circular prescribes the guidelines, rules and regulations on OJT requirements; deployment and completion of on-the-job training. It shall apply student trainees at MIAA and to all MIAA offices that will accommodate students trainees.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div><strong>III. DEFINITION AND TERMS</strong></div>\n<div>    1. On-the-Job Training (OJT) – a time-bounded educational and hands-on work experience for students at MIAA.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div><strong>IV. POLICIES AND PROCEDURES</strong></div>\n<div>\n\n   A. POLICIES\n\n1. School Endorsement\n\n2. Bases of Deployment\n\n3. Discontinuation of On-the-Job Training\n\n4. Remunerationh\n\n5. Attire\n\n6. Working Hours\n\n7. Daily time Record (DTR)\n\nB. PROCEDURES\n\n1. Screening\n<div>         • All on-the-Job training applicants shall undergo a preliminary interview to be conducted the HRDD Representative.</div>\n<div>         • On-the-job training applicants shall submit the following requirements:</div>\na.) School Recommendation\n\nb.) Application Letter stating:\n<div>                      •  Objectives/s</div>\n<div>                      •  Area/s of interest</div>\nc.) Resume\n\nd.) Recent pictures – 2x2 (2 pcs.); 3R half body (1 pc.)\n\ne.) Waiver\n\nf.) NBI Clearance – Original copy and 2 photocopies\n\n•  The said documents shall be reviewed for completeness and evaluated by the Supervisor of HRDD.\n\n• After the requirements have been completed and reviewed on-the-job training applicants shall undergo an interview with the Manager or Supervisor of HRDD.\n<div>       •  Results of Interview shall only be either Pass or Fail.</div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div><strong>V. SUPERSESSION CLAUSE</strong></div>\n<div>    All MIAA issuance in conflict herewith are superseded accordingly.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div><strong>VI. EFFECTIVITY</strong></div>\n<div>     This Memorandum Circular shall take effect immediately.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Guidelines', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '197-revision', '', '', '2013-06-29 15:57:24', '2013-06-29 15:57:24', '', 197, 'http://localhost/wordpress/197-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
